+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DNASjPoi6zBKPCvMrbVUqc","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Phase 10: Recurring Tasks\n     2→\n     3→Add the ability to schedule tasks that recur on a regular interval using simple cron-like expressions.\n     4→\n     5→## Requirements\n     6→\n     7→- A schedule associates a cron expression with a queue and a task template (the payload to use each time).\n     8→- Support a simple subset of cron expressions:\n     9→  - `*/N * * * *` -- every N minutes\n    10→  - `0 * * * *` -- every hour on the hour\n    11→  - `0 0 * * *` -- every day at midnight\n    12→- There should be a way to create, remove, and list active schedules.\n    13→- A manual \"tick\" or \"check\" mechanism should evaluate all active schedules and enqueue tasks for any that are due. This is used for testing.\n    14→- Once enqueued, recurring tasks are regular tasks subject to all other queue rules.\n    15→- Removing a schedule stops future occurrences from being created.\n    16→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01RWHF83NTaazH6dnfMmobxD","session_id":"6757576c-4dba-480a-a31e-dbb8273368b4","uuid":"17f0827c-26ca-4da6-a29f-1e2f615c97e8"}
