`, `dist/`, `*.tsbuildinfo`\n\n---\n\n## Phase Requirements (12 Phases)\n\nAll phase files are located in `/workspace/phases/`\n\n### Phase 1: Basic FIFO Queue\n**File:** `/workspace/phases/phase-01.md`\n\nCore functionality:\n- Accept tasks with payloads\n- Return task objects with unique IDs (UUID), status, and creation timestamp\n- Tasks start in \"pending\" state\n- Retrieve oldest pending task → transition to \"processing\"\n- Return `null` if no tasks available\n- Query task count\n\n### Phase 2: Named Queues\n**File:** `/workspace/phases/phase-02.md`\n\nExtensions:\n- Multiple independent queues by name\n- Default queue if no name provided\n- Implicit queue creation on first task\n- List all queue names\n- Per-queue independence\n- Backward compatibility with Phase 1\n\n### Phase 3: Priority\n**File:** `/workspace/phases/phase-03.md`\n\nFeatures:\n- Priority levels: 1 (highest) to 10 (lowest), default 5\n- Higher-priority (lower number) tasks processed first\n- Same priority → FIFO order\n- Validate priority range (1-10)\n- Per-queue priority ordering\n- Expose priority in task object\n\n### Phase 4: Delayed and Scheduled Tasks\n**File:** `/workspace/phases/phase-04.md`\n\nCapabilities:\n- Specify delay (milliseconds) or future timestamp\n- Delayed tasks added immediately but unavailable until time passes\n- Non-delayed tasks preferred over unavailable delayed tasks\n- Multiple simultaneous delayed tasks ordered by: time → priority → FIFO\n- Task exposes availability time\n- Works with named queues\n\n### Phase 5: Retry with Backoff\n**File:** `/workspace/phases/phase-05.md`\n\nMechanisms:\n- Mark tasks as completed or failed\n- Failed tasks retry automatically with delay if retries remain\n- Exponential backoff: `baseDelay * 2^(attempt - 1)` (default: 1s, 2s, 4s, ...)\n- Max retries: 3 (configurable per task)\n- Base delay: 1000ms (configurable per task)\n- Track attempt count\n- Retried tasks keep original queue and priority\n- Failed tasks remain failed when retries exhausted\n\n### Phase 6: Dead Letter Queue (DLQ)\n**File:** `/workspace/phases/phase-06.md`\n\nAdditions:\n- Tasks with exhausted retries → auto-moved to DLQ\n- View all dead-lettered tasks per queue\n- DLQ retains error information and failure count\n- Re-queue dead-lettered tasks for fresh retry attempts\n- Clear all DLQ tasks per queue\n- Independent DLQ per named queue\n\n### Phase 7: Task Dependencies\n**File:** `/workspace/phases/phase-07.md`\n\nFeatures:\n- Specify task IDs as dependencies\n- Task blocked until dependencies complete\n- Auto-check for unblocked tasks when dependency completes\n- Detect and reject circular dependencies at creation time\n- Error on non-existent task dependencies\n- Failed dependencies DON'T auto-fail dependents (remain blocked)\n- Inspect task dependency status\n\n### Phase 8: Concurrency Control\n**File:** `/workspace/phases/phase-08.md`\n\nControls:\n- Per-queue maximum concurrency limit\n- If limit reached, `getTask()` returns `null` even if pending tasks exist\n- Completing/failing task frees concurrency slot\n- Default: unlimited concurrency\n- Query concurrency limit and current active count\n- Highest-priority available task chosen subject to limit\n\n### Phase 9: Progress Tracking and Cancellation\n**File:** `/workspace/phases/phase-09.md`\n\nFeatures:\n- Processing tasks report progress as percentage (0-100) with optional message\n- Query task progress\n- Subscribe to progress updates (receive notifications)\n- Cancellable subscriptions (unsubscribe)\n- Cancel pending or processing tasks\n- Cancelled pending tasks → removed from queue\n- Cancelled processing tasks → status updated\n- Cancelled tasks never retried\n\n### Phase 10: Recurring Tasks\n**File:** `/workspace/phases/phase-10.md`\n\nScheduling:\n- Cron-like schedules with queue and payload template\n- Supported cron subset:\n  - `*/N * * * *` → every N minutes\n  - `0 * * * *` → every hour on the hour\n  - `0 0 * * *` → every day at midnight\n- Create, remove, and list schedules\n- Manual \"tick\" mechanism to evaluate and enqueue due tasks\n- Recurring tasks subject to all other queue rules\n- Removing schedule stops future occurrences\n\n### Phase 11: Middleware Pipeline\n**File:** `/workspace/phases/phase-11.md`\n\nPipeline:\n- Per-queue middleware registration\n- Task passes through all middleware in order before handler\n- Middleware receives task and \"next\" function\n- Not calling \"next\" skips processing\n- Middleware can modify task\n- Middleware errors → task marked failed\n- Per-queue handler registered\n- Independent middleware stack per queue\n\n### Phase 12: Graceful Shutdown\n**File:** `/workspace/phases/phase-12.md`\n\nShutdown:\n- Signal system to stop accepting new tasks\n- New task additions error after shutdown initiated\n- Wait for processing tasks to complete (configurable timeout)\n- Force-cancel unfinished tasks after timeout\n- Shutdown callbacks during process\n- Summary: completed, force-cancelled, duration\n- Safe multiple calls (same result)\n- Immediate completion if no processing tasks\n\n---\n\n## Source Code Status\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/src/`\n\n- **Current State:** Empty (only `.gitkeep` file present)\n- **Entry Point:** Must export main API from `src/index.ts`\n- **Ready for Implementation:** All configuration and tooling is in place\n\n---\n\n## Key Project Specifications\n\n1. **Type:** TypeScript ES Module project\n2. **Runtime Environment:** Node.js 16+\n3. **No External Runtime Dependencies:** Only dev dependencies allowed\n4. **Build Output:** TypeScript compiles to `./dist`\n5. **Testing:** Vitest with 10-second timeout\n6. **Linting:** ESLint with TypeScript rules\n7. **Development Stack:** Pre-installed and ready (no `npm install` needed)\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nThis is a greenfield TypeScript project for building an in-memory task queue system. The project is structured as 12 incrementally complex phases, starting from basic FIFO queueing and ending with graceful shutdown capabilities. All configuration files are in place, tooling is pre-installed, and the `src/` directory awaits implementation. The project emphasizes extensible design to accommodate future feature additions without reworking foundations."}],"totalDurationMs":37694,"totalTokens":21431,"totalToolUseCount":24,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":192,"cache_read_input_tokens":18986,"output_tokens":2253,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":192,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[]}}}
